    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term referring to all apple trees other than those cultivated for fruit, generally having smaller and more tart fruit than the cultivated varieties.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
